derivation.yuyuan_name: late 16th cent.: from Dutch gabbelen, of imitative origin

entry.def: If you gabble, you say things so quickly that it is difficult for people to understand you.

example.ex: Marcello sat on his knee and gabbled excitedly...
example.tran: 马塞洛跪坐在地上，激动地哇哩哇啦地说着。

example.ex: She gabbles on about drug dealers and journalists...
example.tran: 她叽里咕噜地说着什么毒贩和记者。

means.word_mean: 1. speak (about unimportant matters) rapidly and incessantly
